radiographic_examinations.findings: Visualized lung bases are clear with no focal consolidation or pleural effusion. Enhancing region in segment VII of the liver consistent with hemangioma noted on prior MRI. Hypoattenuating lesion in segment IV of the liver likely represents a simple cyst. Small hypodensity within the right lobe of the liver is too small to characterize. The appendix is approximately 6 mm with no surrounding fat stranding and no definite contrast seen within the appendix. Multilevel degenerative changes in osseous structures.
